# Show Card Rule

This rule defines the required content structure for a "show-card" in the Web3 Wiki, used to showcase a particular project, tool, or service.

## Content Structure

```markdown
#show-card

## Project Overview
- Brief description of the project/tool/service
- Core purpose and value proposition
- Key features and functionalities

## Technical Details
- Underlying technology or blockchain (if applicable)
- Architecture overview
- Unique selling points or innovations

## Use Cases
- Main applications and how it's used
- Target audience or users
- Examples or success stories (if available)

## Getting Started
- How to use or access the project/tool/service
- Links to official website, documentation, and community channels
- Basic setup or integration steps (if applicable)

## Related Links (Optional)
- Links to relevant explain-cards (e.g., [[Underlying Technology]])
- Comparisons with similar projects (if objective and informative)
```

## Formatting Guidelines
- The card must start with the `#show-card` tag on the first line.
- Use H2 (##) for main section titles.
- Use bullet points (-) for sub-items.
- Use Obsidian's internal linking format `[[Page Name]]` for backlinks.
- Provide external links to official resources where appropriate.
